author: stevel
msg: axis-user complaint: the nightly builds wont work on pre1.4 jvms no more.

java1.3 and below had no StringBuffer.append(StringBuffer), but did have StringBuffer.append(Object). So on a 1.3 build this code maps to the Object call, toString() is called and all is well. But on a 1.4 build the new method is used instead, so it aint there at runtime. I wonder how many other places this happens. And I wonder if IDEA has a way to tell me...
